msgctxt "180_Hana"
msgid "Oh, Chief! Out wandering around as usual, I see."
msgstr "¡Jefe! ¿Vagando por ahí como siempre?"

msgctxt "192_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, I don't know about \"wandering around.\" I'm a busy guy,\r\n"
"you know?"
msgstr "Bueno, no le diría \"vagar\". Soy un tipo ocupado,\r\n"
"¿Sabes?"

msgctxt "204_Hana"
msgid "Oh, spare me! You were off playing pachinko or something,\r\n"
"weren't you!?"
msgstr "¡Oh, vamos! Estabas fuera jugando al pachinko o algo,\r\n"
"¡¿Verdad?!"

msgctxt "216_Hana"
msgid "Do you have any idea how many jobs I took care of while you\r\n"
"were out goofing around?"
msgstr "¿Tienes idea de cuánto trabajé mientras holgazaneabas?"

msgctxt "228_Hana"
msgid "Meanwhile, the world keeps turning. Apparently, some\r\n"
"counterfeit bills have been making their way around town.\r\n"
"I saw it on a news site."
msgstr "Mientras el mundo gira. Recientemente, esparcieron.\r\n"
"billetes falsos por la ciudad. Lo vi en un sitio web."

msgctxt "252_Akiyama"
msgid "Aha! So you've been surfing the net all day, have you?"
msgstr "¡Aja! Así que has estado en internet todo el día, ¿No?"

msgctxt "264_Hana"
msgid "I've been gathering info for work!"
msgstr "¡Recopilaba información para el trabajo!"

msgctxt "276_Akiyama"
msgid "Whatever you say... Counterfeit bills, huh? That's bad for\r\n"
"business..."
msgstr "Como digas... Billetes falsos, ¿Eh? Eso es malo para\r\n"
"el negocio..."

msgctxt "288_Hana"
msgid "Tell me about it! I hope they catch the crook soon."
msgstr "¡Ni me lo digas! Espero que atrapen al culpable."

msgctxt "300_Akiyama"
msgid "I'm sure Tokyo's finest are on the case."
msgstr "Seguramente los mejores oficiales de Tokio\r\n"
"investigan el caso."

msgctxt "312_Akiyama"
msgid "*yawn*"
msgstr "*bosteza*"

msgctxt "324_Hana"
msgid "Why do I even bother...?"
msgstr "¿Para qué me molesto...?"

msgctxt "372_Man"
msgid "Hello?"
msgstr "Oi."

msgctxt "384_Hana"
msgid "Oh, hello. Chief! We've got a customer."
msgstr "Oh, hola. ¡Jefe! Tenemos un cliente."

msgctxt "396_Akiyama"
msgid "Oh yeah? Who is it?"
msgstr "¿Ah, sí? ¿Quién es?"

msgctxt "408_Akiyama"
msgid "Ah, Hayashida-san. Is it payback day already?"
msgstr "Ah, Hayashida-san. ¿Ya es día de paga?"

msgctxt "420_Hana"
msgid "Ugh, I wish you'd keep track of these things..."
msgstr "Uh, me gustaría que seas mas atento con esas cosas..."

msgctxt "432_Hayashida"
msgid "Here's this month's payment."
msgstr "Aquí tiene la paga del mes."

msgctxt "444_Akiyama"
msgid "Thank you. Just give me a moment to make sure we're all\r\n"
"squared away..."
msgstr "Gracias. Dame un momento para comprobar que todo esté\r\n"
"en orden..."

msgctxt "504_Hana"
msgid "You're always so prompt with your payments, Hayashida-san.\r\n"
"We really appreciate it."
msgstr "Siempre es tan puntual con sus pagos, Hayashida-san.\\r \n"
"Se lo agradecemos mucho."

msgctxt "516_Hayashida"
msgid "Times are tough, so it certainly hasn't been easy...\r\n"
"But I've managed to hang in there."
msgstr "No son tiempos fáciles...\r\n"
"Pero me las he arreglado para llegar a tiempo."

msgctxt "528_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, in this line of business, you're a rare bird, as far\r\n"
"as customers go."
msgstr "Bueno, en este tipo de negocios eres un cliente raro de\r\n"
"encontrar."

msgctxt "540_Akiyama"
msgid "...Huh?"
msgstr "... ¿Eh?"

msgctxt "552_Akiyama"
msgid "Hayashida-san, did you, by any chance, withdraw this money\r\n"
"from an ATM?"
msgstr "Hayashida-san, por casualidad, ¿Retiraste este dinero\r\n"
"de un cajero automático?"

msgctxt "564_Hayashida"
msgid "No, I took it from the safe at work..."
msgstr "No, lo tome de la caja fuerte de mi tienda..."

msgctxt "576_Hana"
msgid "You run a restaurant, don't you? A French restaurant! Ooh,\r\n"
"I've got to try it out sometime."
msgstr "Tienes un restaurante, ¿Cierto? ¡Un restaurante francés!,\r\n"
"Ooh, tengo que probarlo alguna vez."

msgctxt "588_Akiyama"
msgid "There are some, uh... counterfeit bills in here."
msgstr "Hay algunos, em... Billetes falsos aquí."

msgctxt "600_Hayashida"
msgid "What!?"
msgstr "¡¿Qué?!"

msgctxt "612_Akiyama"
msgid "They're actually pretty well done. Definitely good enough to\r\n"
"fool the eye... Probably couldn't fool an ATM, though."
msgstr "Está bastante bien hecho. Definitivamente podría engañar\r\n"
"al ojo... Aunque, no creo que burle a un cajero automático."

msgctxt "624_Hana"
msgid "Counterfeit bills? Like the ones I just read about online?"
msgstr "¿Billetes falsos? ¡¿Como lo que acabo de leer en línea?!"

msgctxt "636_Akiyama"
msgid "Could be... And I'm thinking we just found the man\r\n"
"responsible."
msgstr "Tal vez... Y creo haber encontrado al culpable."

msgctxt "648_Hayashida"
msgid "What are you saying!?"
msgstr "¡¿Qué estás diciendo?!"

msgctxt "660_Akiyama"
msgid "Sorry. Bad joke. I doubt you'd knowingly use fake bills. I'm\r\n"
"sure you're beyond reproach."
msgstr "Lo siento, lo siento. Solo bromeo. Seguramente no sabías\r\n"
"que eran falsos. No te preocupes."

msgctxt "672_Hayashida"
msgid "Of course I am! I've been working my fingers to the bone to\r\n"
"pay back this money! Why would I try to swindle my way out\r\n"
"now!?"
msgstr "¡Obviamente! ¡He trabajado día y noche para pagar mi deuda!\r\n"
"¡¿Por que intentaría algo así?!"

msgctxt "684_Akiyama"
msgid "Exactly. Do you remember when you got this money?"
msgstr "Exacto. Hayashida-san, ¿Recuerda donde consiguió el dinero?"

msgctxt "696_Hayashida"
msgid "Let's see... Sorry, I'm a little frazzled...  Last week, I\r\n"
"deposited everything at the bank, so this must've happened\r\n"
"sometime after that."
msgstr "Veamos... Lo siento, estoy exhausto... En la semana pasada\r\n"
"deposité todo en el banco, debió suceder luego de eso."

msgctxt "708_Akiyama"
msgid "Well, that helps narrow it down. Any suspicious customers\r\n"
"come by this past week?"
msgstr "Bueno, eso ayuda. ¿Has tenido algún cliente sospechoso?"

msgctxt "720_Hayashida"
msgid "Suspicious customers?"
msgstr "¿Cliente sospechoso?"

msgctxt "732_Akiyama"
msgid "Say, someone who ordered a thousand yen dish and paid with a ten thousand yen bill?"
msgstr "Digamos, ¿Alguien ordenó un plato de mil yenes y pagó con un billete de diez mil?"

msgctxt "744_Hayashida"
msgid "Sure, that happens pretty often..."
msgstr "Claro, eso pasa mucho..."

msgctxt "756_Akiyama"
msgid "Anybody ask you to break big bills as they paid?"
msgstr "¿Alguien pidió cambiar dinero al pagar?"

msgctxt "768_Hayashida"
msgid "Yes! There was somebody like that a couple days ago.\r\n"
"I couldn't exactly say no..."
msgstr "¡Sí! Hubo alguien así hace unos días.\r\n"
"No pude decir que no y tuve que aceptar..."

msgctxt "780_Akiyama"
msgid "That might be our man. Do you remember what he looked like?"
msgstr "Ese podría ser nuestro hombre. ¿Recuerdas cómo era?"

msgctxt "792_Hayashida"
msgid "He struck me as kind of a yakuza type, and he was pretty\r\n"
"intimidating, so it was kinda hard for me to turn him\r\n"
"down..."
msgstr "Parecía una especie de yakuza, y era bastante intimidante,\r\n"
"así que fue difícil para mí rechazarle..."

msgctxt "804_Hana"
msgid "That's got to be him! Super shady!"
msgstr "¡Sospechoso! ¡Debe ser ese tipo!"

msgctxt "816_Akiyama"
msgid "Very interesting. Now let me ask you this. Are you much of\r\n"
"an artist, Hayashida-san?"
msgstr "Interesante. Ahora, déjame preguntarte algo.\r\n"
"¿Eres bueno dibujando, Hayashida-san?"

msgctxt "828_Hayashida"
msgid "Me? I don't draw very well, no..."
msgstr "¿Yo? No, no lo creo..."

msgctxt "840_Akiyama"
msgid "Ah, I see. Well, I'm no Picasso myself. So that just\r\n"
"leaves..."
msgstr "Ah, ya veo. Bueno, yo tampoco soy Picasso. Entonces,\r\n"
"confiamos en..."

msgctxt "852_Hana"
msgid "Who, me?"
msgstr "... ¿Yo?"

msgctxt "864_Akiyama"
msgid "Yep. It's your time to shine, Hana-chan. Show us what you\r\n"
"can do."
msgstr "Sep. Es tu momento de brillar, Hana-chan. Muéstranos lo\r\n"
"que puedes hacer."

msgctxt "876_Hana"
msgid "Well, uh, all right..."
msgstr "Bueno, am, está bien..."

msgctxt "888_Akiyama"
msgid "Hayashida-san, would you please describe this customer?\r\n"
"Whatever you can remember."
msgstr "Hayashida-san, ¿Podrías describir al cliente?\r\n"
"Con lo que recuerdes."

msgctxt "900_Hayashida"
msgid "Let's see. He was about forty years old and..."
msgstr "Veamos. Aparentaba tener unos cuarenta años..."

msgctxt "912_Hana"
msgid "Uh-huh...  Forty years old..."
msgstr "Ajam... Cuarenta años..."

msgctxt "972_Hayashida"
msgid "That's about all I can remember..."
msgstr "Es todo lo puedo recordar..."

msgctxt "984_Hana"
msgid "I see... So, something like this?"
msgstr "Ya veo... Así que, ¿Se veía algo así?"

msgctxt "996_Akiyama"
msgid "......"
msgstr "......"

msgctxt "1008_Hayashida"
msgid "...Ahem."
msgstr "... Pfff."

msgctxt "1020_Hana"
msgid "Hm? What's wrong?"
msgstr "¿Hm? ¿Que pasa?"

msgctxt "1032_Akiyama"
msgid "So we're looking for some kind of ogre...?"
msgstr "Entonces, ¿El culpable es... Un ogro...?"

msgctxt "1044_Hayashida"
msgid "Oh, I don't know... It does kind of look like him."
msgstr "Oh, no lo sé... Pero tiene un parecido a él."

msgctxt "1056_Akiyama"
msgid "Really!? You sure you're not just being polite?"
msgstr "¡¿En serio?! No hace falta que seas educado."

msgctxt "1068_Hana"
msgid "Oh, come on! You told me to draw, so I did!"
msgstr "¡Oh, vamos! ¡Dijiste que dibuje y eso hice!"

msgctxt "1080_Akiyama"
msgid "Hahaha! Forgive me, I had no idea you were so bad at it.\r\n"
"Ahem... Now then, Hayashida-san, do you really see a\r\n"
"resemblance?"
msgstr "¡Ja, ja, ja! Perdón, perdón, no pensé que eras tan mala\r\n"
"dibujando. Ejem... Bien, Hayashida-san,\r\n"
"¿Realmente ves un parecido?"

msgctxt "1092_Hayashida"
msgid "Yes... As a matter of fact, I do."
msgstr "Si... Lo digo en serio."

msgctxt "1104_Akiyama"
msgid "I see... And here I thought I was a man of the world..."
msgstr "Ya veo... Nunca se sabe que encontraremos en el mundo..."

msgctxt "1116_Hana"
msgid "Chief..."
msgstr "Jefe..."

msgctxt "1128_Akiyama"
msgid "Never mind. Hana-chan, can you make me some copies of this?\r\n"
"About fifty or so should do."
msgstr "Da igual. Hana-chan, haz copias de esto.\r\n"
"Unas cincuenta bastarán."

msgctxt "1140_Hana"
msgid "Like I'm not embarrassed enough? Look, I'll make the copies,\r\n"
"but don't tell me you're going to try and find this guy\r\n"
"yourself?"
msgstr "¿Eh? Como si no estuviera lo suficientemente avergonzada.\r\n"
"De acuerdo, las haré. Presidente, ¿Está usted intentando\r\n"
"encontrarlo?"

msgctxt "1152_Akiyama"
msgid "Thinkin' about it..."
msgstr "Ando dándole vueltas..."

msgctxt "1164_Hayashida"
msgid "Oh, you don't have to go that far! I'll replace the fakes\r\n"
"right away. Besides, wouldn't this be better left in the\r\n"
"hands of the police?"
msgstr "¿Qué? ¡No tienes que ir tan lejos!. Voy a\\r \n"
"reemplazar las falsificaciones de inmediato. Aparte,\\r \n"
"¿No seria mejor dejarlo en manos de la policía?"

msgctxt "1176_Akiyama"
msgid "Don't worry. I'll take care of it. I'll be in touch if I\r\n"
"find out anything."
msgstr "Tranquilo. Yo me encargo. Te aviso si encuentro algo."

msgctxt "1188_Hayashida"
msgid "If you say so... I suppose I'll be on my way, then."
msgstr "Como digas... Si me disculpan, debo irme."

msgctxt "1248_Hana"
msgid "I've got your copies ready. Are you really gonna go look\r\n"
"for this guy?"
msgstr "Tengo las copias listas. Pero jefe, ¿De verdad va a buscar\r\n"
"al culpable?"

msgctxt "1260_Akiyama"
msgid "That's the plan."
msgstr "Así es."

msgctxt "1272_Hana"
msgid "What do you want to do that for? Weren't you just talking\r\n"
"about how \"Tokyo's finest\" were on the case?"
msgstr "¿Por que te preocupas ahora? ¿No decías que\r\n"
"\"los mejores oficiales de Tokio\" seguían el caso?"

msgctxt "1284_Akiyama"
msgid "I did intend to let them handle it, yes. But it's a\r\n"
"different story when one of my customers is involved."
msgstr "Esa era mi intención. Sin embargo, es diferente ahora.\r\n"
"Uno de mis clientes está envuelto."

msgctxt "1296_Akiyama"
msgid "My customers' money holds a deep significance to them. For\r\n"
"Hayashida-san, it's the tangible fruit of all the hard work\r\n"
"he puts into making delicious food."
msgstr "El dinero de mis clientes tiene un significado para ellos.\r\n"
"Para Hayashida-san, es fruto de su esfuerzo por hacer\r\n"
"la comida mas deliciosa."

msgctxt "1308_Akiyama"
msgid "Way I see it, fake money is like spitting in the face of\r\n"
"everyone who puts in a hard day's work, and well...\r\n"
"Frankly, it pisses me off."
msgstr "Para mi, el dinero falso es como escupir en quienes\r\n"
"se esfuerzan todos los días trabajando duro.\r\n"
"Eso, francamente, me jode mucho."

msgctxt "1320_Hana"
msgid "Chief..."
msgstr "Jefe..."

msgctxt "1332_Akiyama"
msgid "I'm not entirely sure this is the culprit, but it's all I\r\n"
"have to go on right now. I'll ask around. Take care of the\r\n"
"the office while I'm gone, all right?"
msgstr "Dudo que el culpable sea realmente así, pero es lo que\r\n"
"tengo. Iré a preguntar por allí. Cuida la oficina mientras\\r \n"
"yo me encargo."

msgctxt "1344_Hana"
msgid "Aw, Chief, can't you at least try to get through some of\r\n"
"this paperwork first...?"
msgstr "Ah, Jefe, ¿No puedes hacer algo de papeleo antes...?"

msgctxt "1404_Akiyama"
msgid "(Hana-chan really slaved over this sketch... Guess I should start handing 'em out.)"
msgstr "(Hana-chan realmente se esforzó con el boceto...\n"
"Creo que empezaré repartiéndolos)"

msgctxt "1416_Akiyama"
msgid "(I'll stop by my friends' places first. Maybe somebody who usually deals in big bills, like the owner of Sushi Gin.)"
msgstr "(Iré a las tiendas de mis amigos. Empezando por el dueño de Sushi Gin, que parece manejar muchos billetes de 10.000)."

